// Page RoguetoHero Text :
"P1650391081" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Pair of Broken Six Sided Dice</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You find a pair of six sided dice, both missing one of their numbers. It looks like someone isn't going to have their dice for a tabletop game tonight. Just when you're about to toss the dice away, you notice that these dice actually link together to form some sort of necklace. On the inside of the dice are the initials, "J" and "M". What stands out more is that the dice reek of perfume from the Carnival of Shadows. You call up one of your contacts to see what you can find out... <br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>{HeroName}, how's it going? Eh? Weird dice with initials in them? Come to think of it, I've heard about a recent kidnapping over there in Paragon. Happened to two kids named Jason and Mary, they're real big into that whole tabletop scene. Hold on, let me dig up some more information...<br><br>Huh. Well, that's too bad for them. Looks like the Carnies picked 'em up hoping to get a ransom out of Jason's dad. Turns out that his father is part of the Family, but he's not making any deals with the Carnies. According to this, the Carnies say they're going to make the girl one of their slaves and butcher the kid. Here's the address of the office they're supposed to be in, seems like the Carnies are carving a hideout for themselves. Just so you know, though, there doesn't look like there's gonna be any money involved in this.</scale></font></color><br><br>It looks like these two innocent players of tabletop games have gotten themselvs in over their head, all because one of them has a father who works for the Family. If the Carnies were in this purely for the money, they'd have just try to cut a different deal, but it's clear to you that they're just trying to cause chaos wherever they can. It's unlikely that the Family could take care of the Carnival, which means if anyone's going to save those two, it's going to have to be you!"
// Answer Text :
"P3147467872" "HERO: Save the Gamers from the Carnival"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


