// Page RoguetoHero Text :
"P250676342" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Deactivated Arachnos Spider</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You pick up a deactivated Arachnos spider and tinker around with it a bit, looking to see if you can pry any information out of it. After a few minutes, you see a hologram shoot up of a pre-recorded message. The person delivering the message is Black Scorpion, who doesn't seem to be too pleased.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>Listen up! You guys have heard of that Savage Siren, right? Well, we're puttin' a stomp on her actions. She's one of them mercenaries that went and stole a bunch of my schematics to sell to the highest bidder! One of our squads has her now, but we're gonna need back up since they're in Paragon.<br><br>You guys make sure to take this spider and get a recording of what's gonna happen to her. We're gonna make an <i>example</i> out of her to all them mercs and rogues in Paragon and the Rogue Isles. You take a job against Arachnos or Black Scorpion and you're gonna <i>pay</i>. And by pay, I mean get ripped <i>limb from limb</i>. After we find out who hired her, of course. Then we'll find the client she's workin' for and rip THEM limb from limb too! That oughta show anyone lookin' to hire them to think twice! Bahahaha! Black Scorpion, OUT.</scale></font></color><br><br>While it might be nice to have some competition eliminated, it won't bode well for business if Savage Siren is savagely killed. No one is going to put out contracts against Arachnos or buy any of their stolen goods if Arachnos manages to get away with this. While a <i>true</i> hero might arrest Savage Siren for her crimes, someone like you might just try to make sure she gets out of there alive. If not, well, then you might see a number of high-priced contracts for Arachnos suddenly dissappear from the market!"
// Answer Text :
"P2558097353" "HERO: Save Savage Siren"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


