// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page RoguetoHero Text :
"P2685010647" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Maniacal Laughter</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You hear nearby the sound of someone laughing madly. You look around, and you continue to hear it...<br><br>GYAAAH-HAH-HAH-HAH-HAH-HAAAAA!!!!<br><br>You finally spot the source of it. An Arachnos radio on the ground. You pick it up and examine the radio. A voice begins to speak, unaware that you're listening.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>AHA! The moment for my dramatic speech! Ahem...<br><br>OVERDRIVE! I see you have fallen into my, Vernon Von Grun's, ULTIMATE trap! BAHAHA! You'll find yourself trapped in the sewers beneath Paragon, SURROUNDED by the Arachnoids! You're probably wondering how you were bested. I'll tell you how - through the power of my SCIENCE! Soon, all of your city will be overrun by the creatures, and there's NOTHING you can do to stop me!<br><br>You might think I'm mad, but YOU'RE the mad one. Do you see what I did there? A final joke to give to you before you die! GYA-HAHAHA!<br><br>... what? .... WHAT?! This is being broadcasted over an OPEN FREQUENCY?! Anyone can hear this?!<br><br>...<br><br>... GAAAAH! YOU FOO-</scale></font></color><br><br>The radio signal suddenly cuts out, presumably from Vernon Von Grun closing the frequency. It sounds as if Overdrive is in some serious trouble. Normally, you wouldn't give the whole deal of rescuing a hero the time of day, but this seems like another one of a series of scenarios where you might not be able to just walk away. Being ripped apart by Arachnoids is definitely a grim way to go, but having the <i>entire</i> city crawling with the creatures is going to cause a lot of innocent people to die. You might not be one for heroics, but this seems like a case where someone needs to roll up their sleeves and do some dirty work to get the job done. Dirty work in this case means 'free' work."
// Answer Text :
"P2853628165" "HERO: Save Overdrive and Paragon from the Arachnoids!"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


