// Page RoguetoHero Text :
"P3128129456" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Hologram of General Aarons</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>While wandering around, a hologram of General Aarons appears in front of you. It seems like there's a small projector on the ground that was triggered by your presence.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>{HeroName}. ... {HeroName}? I told Blast Furnace to come to this location... not what I was expecting, but it'll have to do. I'm aware of your status as a sword for hire, but in this situation, you're the only person who can help.<br><br>Vanguard has been given authority to utilize some of Longbow's sea bases for storage. I was at one for a meeting when we were attacked by Cole's soldiers, the Imperial Defense Force. I've managed to keep myself hidden, but their forces will capture me at any moment.<br><br>I understand that you're not one to do things for free, but we're in a dire situation at the moment. The Praetorians are ransacking this base for any information Vanguard has on them. If they manage to get their hands on both me and the information, it could spell disaster for the war effort against the Praetorians: they'll find out about the numerous Vanguard operatives that are currently undercover in Praetoria. Here is the location of the base. You're the only person who can get in here quick enough and give us a hand.<br><br>Please, {HeroName}, put aside your desire for money to help our world against Tyrant. Or, at the very least, to protect the lives of those men and women working for Vanguard in Praetoria. </scale></font></color><br><br>The hologram of General Aarons vanishes, leaving you with a decision. Yet again, someone is asking you to do something for free. It must be the general vibe of Paragon, given how all these heroes run around without asking a cent for their help. However, it seems like this is a serious threat that needs to be handled. If Emperor Cole manages to get that information, it could mean that a lot of lives will be lost over there in Praetoria. Not to mention how difficult it would be to make an 'honest' living if the entire world is turned into a police state."
// Answer Text :
"P379868482" "HERO: Rescue General Aarons!"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


